fallacy /ˈfæləsɪ/

(fallacies) 

1. N-VAR A fallacy is an idea which many people believe to be true, but which is in fact false because it is based on incorrect information or reasoning. 谬见 

例： It's a fallacy that the affluent give relatively more to charity than the less prosperous. 富人比不太有钱的人给慈善机构相对更多捐赠是一种谬见。

